            <p>State of New York.<lb/>
                Assembly Chamber.<lb/>
                Albany.<lb/></p>
            <p>March 13&#47;91<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Dr<lb/></p>
            <p>Excuse my not sooner<lb/> replying to your several favors&#45;&#45;<lb/> I at once saw Rev Nieto&#44; and<lb/> he promised me <hi rend="underline">positively</hi> to<lb/> take active steps towards finding<lb/> a proper home for Wiener&#45;&#45;he<lb/> even said that he would try to<lb/> have Wiener with his daughter&#44;<lb/> married &#38; keeping house&#45;&#45;he<lb/> has since written to me that he<lb/> hopes to arrange it very shortly&#45;&#45;<lb/> I have also spoken to Dr Mendes<lb/> as to it&#45;&#45;I hope it will soon<lb/> be all right&#45;&#45;I suppose<lb/> you get monthly reports from<lb/> Dr Drachman &#38; Dr Lieberman.<lb/>  Yours Truly<lb/> Joseph Blumenthal<lb/></p>
            <p>over<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Dr Drachman suggests<lb/> that the Hazan of his<lb/> Congregation&#44; shall<lb/> teach Hazanoth in<lb/> the Seminary&#45;&#45;<lb/>  What think you<lb/> of it&#45;&#45;if<lb/> favorably&#44; arrange<lb/> the matter with<lb/> Dr D<lb/></p>
